pr_title: frontend starter and endpoint for new test history grid
pr_body:
<!--
Thanks for the PR, you probably worked hard on it! Before you submit it for review, please make sure you read our guidelines for contributing to this repository. 

Try to make the job easy for your reviewer! Below is a template you can use as a guide for what context your reviewer might need.  
If you changed any dev procedures, consider also updating the README.
-->

## Description
This pr includes a starter endpoint for populating mock data for showing test history in order to populate a timeline chart using [google charts](https://developers.google.com/chart/interactive/docs/gallery/timeline)

![image](https://github.com/web-platform-tests/wpt.fyi/assets/52478074/209f0f20-fc13-4942-b303-75b09924724b)

Updates from feedback:
- [x] Convert to timeline layout from grid layout
- [x] Integrate google charts
- [x] Expand mock data to include other browsers
- [x] Add copyright to new history grid file
- [x] Hide new chart button behind feature flag
- [x] Integrate css global paper colors
- [x] handle resize bug
- [x] Update endpoint to handle POST requests that take a test name param, instead of GET requests (fixed in #3411)
- [x] Fix links on chart navigating to bad URLs (fixed in #3410)

pr_title: Fix links on chart navigating to bad URLs
pr_body: This PR fixes an issue on #3368 where individual test run links were returning undefined. This bug happened when the mock data was changed from depicting one set of browser data to four. The chart reference variable was being overwritten for each individual chart, therefore only the links in the final chart were still functional. These changes ensure that the chart for each browser is stored in an array and can be indexed as needed.

This PR alters the existing `/api/history` endpoint to accept POST requests rather than GET requests. This is due to GET requests supporting a finite URL length. The POST request body will give us more flexibility with what information can be sent along with the request.

pr_title: Get data from local datastore instead of from mock JSON
pr_body: This PR adds logic to populate temporary fake data into the local environment datastore. Previously it has been pulling mock data from a static JSON file. It is now pulling from and processing data from a mock data set in the local version of the datastore.

pr_title: update dev data and mock json to use ISO date format
pr_body: This PR fixes a bug where the new test history timeline was displaying date information incorrectly, due to the date being in the incorrect format. This PR changes all of the mock data dates to ISO format.

This PR fixes issue #3443. There was an issue where timeline charts were sometimes getting data for the incorrect browser. In this PR I have changed the data to be represented in a map that is accessed via browser name, rather than indexed in an array. This should assure that each chart is always getting the correct browser data.

pr_title: Refresh history data when page is changed
pr_body: This PR solves issue #3446 where the same data was persisting for different tests. I solved this by checking for and clearing any existing data before running the query for new data. I also added logic to hide the history timelines when a new test page is visited after viewing a previous one.

pr_title: Add date sort to history handler
pr_body: This PR fixes issue #3462 sorting the datastore run results by date.

This PR fixes issue #3450. Previous iterations of the timeline had a fixed height. The height of the timeline chart is now calculated by the number of subtests, unless there are more than 20, in which case it will add a scroll bar. This PR also fixes a bug where some charts were breaking due to missing data.

pr_body:
This PR fixes issue #3473 by correcting the order in which subtests appear. Previously they were appearing in alphabetical order. Now the subtest names are being imported from the row info on the table above, so they should appear in the same order.

Edit: Logic refactored to use event listeners instead of two-way data binding.
